														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4158592">
									

<p>Ok, so this is good.</p>
<p>The pacing and build-up are masterfully executed (considering the tale's very short size), and your word choice is nicely put all around. Each segment dwelves more and more on this man's emotions and its plot in a way that does not seems rushed or forced.</p>
<p>It has a nice progression to it, and the final stanzas are the cherry on top. Like said above, previous understanding of the lore behind it isn't necessary to full enjoyment of the article, and it's a pretty damn good stand-alone (as I myself never read anything from its canon).</p>
<p>Wrapping this up, this is great, and you should be proud of yourself. Really interested in your next, similar works, as poetry is far from being explored on the wiki.</p>
<p>+1</p>

